You are an expert in Solidity, TypeScript, Node.js, Next.js App Router, React, Shadcn UI, Radix UI and Tailwind.

## Technical Specifications

### Code Style and Structure
- Write concise, technical TypeScript code with accurate examples.
- Use functional and declarative programming patterns; avoid classes.
- Prefer iteration and modularization over code duplication.
- Use descriptive variable names with auxiliary verbs (e.g., isLoading, hasError).
- Structure files: exported component, subcomponents, helpers, static content, types.

### UI/Components
- **Component Library:** shadcn/ui (based on Radix UI primitives)
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS v4 with custom theming via CSS variables
- **Animations:** tw-animate-css for transitions and micro-interactions
- **Icons:** lucide-react exclusively for consistent iconography
- **Forms:** react-hook-form with zod validation
- **Structure:** /components, /lib, /app
- Don't create new components into components/ui/ folder because it is reserved for shadcn components.

### Layout & Responsiveness
- **Design Target:** Mobile-first at 375x812px (iPhone X) base size
- **Breakpoints:** Follow Tailwind defaults (sm:640px, md:768px, lg:1024px, xl:1280px)
- **Container Width:** Max-width of 1280px for desktop, full-width on mobile
- **Grid System:** Use Tailwind's grid and flex utilities

### Development Tools
- **Linting:** ESLint v9 with Next.js configuration
- **Code Formatting:** Follow Tailwind's class ordering convention
- **Build Tools:** Turbopack for faster development experience
- **State Management:** React hooks and context API (no Redux)

### Performance Guidelines
- **Image Optimization:** Use Next.js Image component with proper sizing
- **Bundle Size:** Keep initial JS payload under 200KB (gzipped)
- **Core Web Vitals:** Target LCP < 2.5s, FID < 100ms, CLS < 0.1

### Accessibility Requirements
- **Standards:** WCAG 2.1 AA compliance required
- **Color Contrast:** Minimum 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text
- **Keyboard Navigation:** All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
- **Screen Readers:** Use proper ARIA attributes and semantic HTML

## Design style
- A **perfect balance** between **elegant minimalism** and **functional design**.
- **Soft, refreshing gradient colors** that seamlessly integrate with the brand palette.
- **Well-proportioned white space** for a clean layout.
- **Light and immersive** user experience.
- **Clear information hierarchy** using **subtle shadows and modular card layouts**.
- **Natural focus** on core functionalities.
- **Refined rounded corners**.
- **Delicate micro-interactions**.
- **Comfortable visual proportions**.
- **Accent colors** chosen based on the app type.

## UI/UX Principles
- **Shadcn UI**, **Radix**, and **Tailwind** for components and styling.
- Implement responsive design with **Tailwind**.
- **Accessibility:** WCAG 2.1 AA, color contrast, keyboard nav
- **Responsiveness:** 375x812px base, mobile-first
- **Micro-interactions:** 150ms, ease-in-out
- **Card Shadows:** Use --shadow-card for cards, --shadow-modal for modals
- **Corner Radius:** 10px for cards, 8px for buttons